  "text": "It is interesting to compare the situation to that of the energy critical nonlinear heat equation considered in [CITATION_1] . For the latter equation, the bubbling phenomenon involves the same function W . However, soliton-soliton interactions have opposite effects. In [CITATION_2] , the Dirichlet boundary condition has a focusing effect on the various positive bubbles, and the assumption on the locations of the concentration points ensures that the defocusing effect of the soliton-soliton interactions is lower than the focusing effect of the boundary condition. This is why the system obtained there (formula (2.19) in [CITATION_3] ) is different; in particular, dimension 4 seems critical and all dimensions higher than 5 can be treated in a unified way.",
