    "119587081": {
      "title": "Green's function and infinite-time bubbling in the critical nonlinear heat equation",
      "abstract": "Let $\\Omega$ be a smooth bounded domain in $\\R^n$, $n\\ge 5$. We consider the semilinear heat equation at the critical Sobolev exponent $$ u_t = \\Delta u + u^{\\frac{n+2}{n-2}} \\inn \\Omega\\times (0,\\infty), \\quad u =0 \\onn \\pp\\Omega\\times (0,\\infty). $$ ::: Let $G(x,y)$ be the Dirichlet Green's function of $-\\Delta$ in $\\Omega$ and $H(x,y)$ its regular part. Let $q_j\\in \\Omega$, $j=1,\\ldots,k$, be points such that the matrix $$ ::: \\left [ \\begin{matrix} H(q_1, q_1) & -G(q_1,q_2) &\\cdots & -G(q_1, q_k) -G(q_1,q_2) & H(q_2,q_2) & -G(q_2,q_3) \\cdots & -G(q_3,q_k) \\vdots & & \\ddots& \\vdots -G(q_1,q_k) &\\cdots& -G(q_{k-1}, q_k) & H(q_k,q_k) \\end{matrix} \\right ] $$ is positive definite. For any $k\\ge 1$ such points indeed exist. We prove the existence of a positive smooth solution $u(x,t)$ which blows-up by bubbling in infinite time near those points. More precisely, for large time $t$, $u$ takes the approximate form $$ u(x,t) \\approx \\sum_{j=1}^k \\alpha_n \\left ( \\frac { \\mu_j(t)} { \\mu_j(t)^2 + |x-\\xi_j(t)|^2 } \\right )^{\\frac {n-2}2} . $$ Here $\\xi_j(t) \\to q_j$ and $0<\\mu_j(t) \\to 0$, as $t \\to \\infty$. We find that $\\mu_j(t) \\sim t^{-\\frac 1{n-4}} $ as $t\\to +\\infty$, when $n\\geq 5$."
    }
